    "long_instructions": "\r\n#### It's important to learn not just how to use AI systems, but also how they work.\r\n\r\n## 📝 To Do\r\n\r\n#### Watch this video clip to hear Mira Murati, former CTO at Open AT, and Cristobal Valenzuela from Runway explain how large language models work. As you watch, listen for the following key vocabulary words.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #B7E0E5; border-radius: 10px; padding: 15px; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 85%; box-sizing: border-box; word-wrap: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 12px; line-height: 120%;\">📖 <strong>Large Language Model (LLM)</strong> is a general purpose form of AI that is trained on a very, very large body of knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 12px; line-height: 120%;\"><strong>📖 Neural Network</strong> is an interconnected network that makes decisions using weights and hidden layers. It is used to represent the relationship between words.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 12px; line-height: 120%;\"><strong>📖 Training</strong> is the process of teaching an AI model by exposing it to large amounts of data, allowing it to learn patterns, improve accuracy, and refine its predictions over time.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8148B2; display: inline-block;\">\r\n    ➡️ This video is from Lesson 3. You can find more details in the full <a href='https://example.com/lesson1' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>Lesson Plan</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n"
  },
